==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tympanohyal
<hw>Tym`pa*no*hy"al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>Of or pertaining to the tympanum and the hyoidean arch.</def> --
<def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>The proximal segment in the hyoidean arch,
becoming a part of the styloid process of the temporal bone in adult
man.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tympanum</ent>⟦br⟧
